-----------------------------------------
ANTI-PHISH EXTENSION – TEST CASES
-----------------------------------------

# 1. URL Heuristic Tests
1.1 Suspicious subdomain detection  
    URL: https://secure-login.example.com  
    Expect: Flagged as suspicious (contains phishing-style subdomain)

1.2 Known phishing keyword in hostname  
    URL: https://account-verify-example.net  
    Expect: Flagged (keyword match: “verify”)

1.3 Safe domain should not be flagged  
    URL: https://google.com  
    Expect: No warning

1.4 Local file phishing demo  
    URL: file:///demo/phishing-sample.html  
    Expect: Flagged (contains credential form)

-----------------------------------------------------

# 2. DOM Credential Form Tests
2.1 Page contains a login form  
    Form fields: email + password  
    Expect: Immediate banner injected ("contains credential form")

2.2 Page contains only username field  
    Expect: No flag

2.3 Page contains multiple sensitive input fields  
    Expect: Flagged

-----------------------------------------------------

# 3. Popup “Scan Tab” Button
3.1 Clicking Scan Tab on a suspicious page  
    Expect:  
        - Status updates to “Scanning…”  
        - Warning sent if credential form exists  
        - Popup displays “scan completed”

3.2 Clicking Scan Tab on a normal page  
    Expect: “No issues found”

3.3 After clicking “Dismiss” → Scan Tab again  
    Expect: Warning banner reappears

-----------------------------------------------------

# 4. Error Handling
4.1 chrome:// or chrome-extension:// pages  
    Expect: Skipped (non-injectable URL)

4.2 New tabs / blank pages  
    Expect: Skipped

4.3 Disallowed pages  
    Expect: “Skipping DOM checks” in console

-----------------------------------------------------

# 5. Persistence
5.1 After reloading extension  
    Expect: All features still work (tested)

5.2 After reopening the browser  
    Expect: Background worker starts and logs initialization

-----------------------------------------------------

End of testcase list.
